---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="EduPath — AI-Driven Learning Platform" description="EduPath uses LLMs to generate personalised learning curricula that adapt to each learner.">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 pt-32 pb-24">

    <a href="/projects" class="text-sm text-slate-500 hover:text-white transition-colors mb-8 inline-block">← All projects</a>

    <div class="mb-2">
      <span class="text-xs font-medium text-green-400 bg-green-950/50 rounded px-2.5 py-1">Live</span>
    </div>
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-white mt-4 mb-2">EduPath</h1>
    <p class="text-xl text-slate-400 mb-10">AI-driven personalised learning platform.</p>

    <div class="space-y-8">

      <div class="rounded-xl border-l-4 border-blue-500 bg-slate-900/60 p-6">
        <p class="text-slate-300 text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium">
          "Learning should adapt to you. Not the other way around."
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-white font-semibold text-xl mb-3">The problem</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
          Most learning platforms give everyone the same content in the same order. That's not how people learn. Some need more context, others need to skip ahead. The content that works for one person bores or overwhelms another.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-white font-semibold text-xl mb-3">What EduPath does</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-3">
          {[
            "Generates a personalised learning curriculum based on your goals and current level",
            "Adapts content complexity and pacing as you progress",
            "Surfaces the right resources at the right time",
            "Tracks progress and identifies gaps proactively",
          ].map(item => (
            <li class="flex gap-3 text-slate-400">
              <span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▸</span>
              <span>{item}</span>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-white font-semibold text-xl mb-3">Status</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
          Validated with real learners. Currently live and expanding — working on additional subject areas and improving the adaptation algorithm based on real usage data.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="mt-14 pt-8 border-t border-slate-800 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      {["EdTech", "LLM", "Product", "React", "Personalisation"].map(tag => (
        <span class="text-xs text-blue-400 bg-blue-950/40 rounded px-2 py-0.5">{tag}</span>
      ))}
    </div>

  </div>
</Layout>
